HEADWORD: Metergram
<hw>Me"ter*gram`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mech.)</fld>
<def>A measure of energy or work done; the power exerted in raising one
gram through the distance of one meter against gravitation; 100
gram-centimeters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metewand</ent>⟦br⟧
